The paper deals with algorithms for sampling from the set of proper k-colourings on random graphs, which is a problem in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.DS). The algorithm is based on spatial mixing properties of colourings, which is a topic in statistical physics (cs.GT) and theoretical computer science (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the efficiency of the algorithm, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT).
